article.headline: BYU escapes with 69-67 win over San Diego

images.name: V. Pusica made Three Point Jumper.
images.caption: 1H (14:59) USD Vasa Pusica made Three Point Jumper.

article.linkText: BYU escapes with 69-67 win over San Diego
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Kyle Collinsworth had 25 points and 12 rebounds and Nick Emery made three late free throws to help BYU escape San Diego 69-67 on Thursday night. Chase Fischer added 14 points and Emery 12 for the Cougars (20-8, 11-4 West Coast Conference), who posted their 11th consecutive 20-win season despite shooting only 35 percent. The Cougars had an eight-point lead before the Toreros (8-18, 3-12) cut it to 66-64 with 48 seconds left. BYU missed a 3-pointer but retained possession on a held-ball. Emery followed with two free throws. USD's Vasa Pusica hit a 3-pointer with seven seconds remaining but Emery added a final free throw, missed a second, and USD's desperation heave wasn't close. Pusica had 17 points, Duda Sanadze 16 and Olin Carter III 15 for USD, which led by 13 with 5:30 remaining in the first half, but then went nearly 10 minutes without scoring.
